================================================================================
README — exp_00X folder
================================================================================
This folder contains all simulation scripts and results for one experiment
(E1, E2, or E3). See exp/meta for the differences between experiments.
================================================================================

CONTENTS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  Sims_all.R        Combined script running all 10 scenarios sequentially
                    in one R session. Data loaded once and shared across all
                    scenarios. Best for a single long screen session.

  sims1.R           Scenario 1:  Non-differential error, Null association
  sims2.R           Scenario 2:  Non-differential error, Harmful association
  sims3.R           Scenario 3:  Differential -- less error in at-risk, Null
  sims4.R           Scenario 4:  Differential -- more error in at-risk, Null
  sims5.R           Scenario 5:  Differential -- less error in at-risk + 50% non-risk, Null
  sims6.R           Scenario 6:  Differential -- more error in at-risk + 50% non-risk, Null
  sims7.R           Scenario 7:  Differential -- less error in at-risk, Harmful
  sims8.R           Scenario 8:  Differential -- more error in at-risk, Harmful
  sims9.R           Scenario 9:  Differential -- less error in at-risk + 50% non-risk, Harmful
  sims10.R          Scenario 10: Differential -- more error in at-risk + 50% non-risk, Harmful

  Results/          Folder where all simulation output CSVs are saved.
                    Also contains VisualizeResults.R (run from inside this folder).

HOW TO RUN
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Scripts must be run from inside this exp_00X folder (not the project root).
See the project-root readme for full screen session instructions.

  Option A — all scenarios in one session (~10-12 hrs):
    Rscript Sims_all.R

  Option B — each scenario in its own parallel screen session (~2.5 hrs total):
    Rscript sims1.R
    Rscript sims2.R
    ...
    Rscript sims10.R
    
  Option c —  Run scenarios individually in parallel using .sh file (~2.5 hrs total) --
    cd ~/Downloads/CodeReview/CodeReview_Heather
    chmod +x run_all_sims.sh   # only first time
    ./run_all_sims.sh # creates 10 screens named simsX and executes each simsX.R in that screen
    screen -ls # to check if all screens created and are running
    

Each sims#.R script is fully self-contained and can be run standalone or
sourced from Sims_all.R — it will detect whether data are already loaded
and skip re-reading from disk if so.

OUTPUTS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Each sims#.R script saves two CSV files to Results/:
  <scenario_name>.csv        200 x (2 * 4) matrix of beta and SE estimates
  cor_<scenario_name>.csv    200 x 4 matrix of correlations (pm.err vs pm25)

After all simulations complete, run VisualizeResults.R from inside Results/
to produce Figure 2, Figure 3, and the data for Tables A3-A5.
